                  <persName id="t18260914-461-person2369">
                  MARY 
                  CRAGG
               <interp inst="t18260914-461-person2369" type="surname" value="CRAGG"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-461-person2369" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-461-person2369" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of John Cragg - we live in <placeName id="t18260914-461-crimeloc2591">Tilburn-street, Thomas-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-461-crimeloc2591" type="placeName" value="Tilburn-street, Thomas-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-461-crimeloc2591" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-461-off2589 t18260914-461-crimeloc2591"></join>; our bed-room is on the first floor, over the stable. On the 8th of September I saw my room door (which I had locked) open and shut softly, and heard a bustle up the second flight of stairs - I went up, and met the prisoner coming down; I said, "You have been into my room" - he said, "I have." I called for assistance - he was secured, and this coat and breeches, which had been in my drawer, were produced; there was nobody else in the house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-461-person2370">
                  MARY 
                  RIVERS
